{{DISPLAYTITLE: Entity 58 - "The Sleep Paralysis Demon"}} 

{{Background|file=Static-tv-static.gif}}
{{Blurimage|file=Entity-58-v2.jpg|width=746×784|align=center|caption=A reconstruction based on a survivor's testimony of the entity's appearance, likely Manifestation 1.}}
=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Overview</center></span>'''==
'''The Sleep Paralysis Demon''', officially assigned the designation of '''Entity 58''', is an entity that peculiarly mirrors the sleep paralysis phenomenon in [[The Frontrooms]], experienced by a minority of individuals. However, unlike the harmless nature of the phenomenon in [[The Frontrooms]], the phenomenon is significantly more harmful when it occurs in [[The Backrooms]]. Due to the extreme difficulty of tracking encounters and collecting testimonies from encounters, it is considered one of the least understood entities within [[The Backrooms]]. '''Entity 58''' often selects wanderers who are sleeping on solid surfaces, such as floors, tables, or chairs, as preferred victims. 

=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Behavior</center></span>'''==
As mentioned before, '''The Sleep Paralysis Demon''' will target any individual who is sleeping on a hard surface. The exact reasoning behind this surface is not fully understood and is still being investigated. However, sleeping on a hard surface is linked to having trouble sleeping, which is a factor in insomnia. Many of the symptoms caused by insomnia are often early predictors of sleep paralysis. 

'''Entity 58''' will manifest once its chosen victim has fallen asleep, usually around 5 to 7 yards (4.6 - 6.4 m) away, once the victim has entered the state of being asleep and awake. There have been rare cases where the entity appears only few inches away from the target; in these cases, death is almost certain, with a 95% mortality rate. But, regardless of distance, the target must maintain eye contact with '''Entity 58''' to prevent predation. The exact length that one must maintain with the entity is yet to be determined.<ref>After consulting and questioning survivors, the general consensus concerning how quickly this entity can advance upon one because of blinking or breaking eye contact depends on the level of fear presented by the victim. </ref> What is known is that blinking or looking away is not always certain death, but survivors do report that the entity will close the distance between the victim and itself. In cases of close proximity, survivors report the following:

*The entity will abruptly startle the victim and take them to an unknown place for an undetermined amount of time.<ref>Although not exactly known, the specific place in question has been reported as a partially dark series of wooden hallways, with many reporting a scopophobia-like feeling. However, this specific description of the place is not connected to any known or existing level.</ref> Nonetheless, this behavioral pattern is rather considered rare and is a clear indicator that this entity harbors sadistic tendencies. But, the reason this entity likes to 'play with its food' is undetermined. 

*'''Entity 58''' will progressively inch closer to its victim and widen its mouth.<ref> This occurrence can only happen when the entity is Manifestation 2; otherwise, it is impossible for this to happen.</ref> Two survivors reported observing a soft, blue glowing light down the creature's throat and experiencing the sensation of relief, tranquility, bliss, and a heavy drowsiness washing over them.

Once the target makes it through staring at '''The Sleep Paralysis Demon''', they will wake up in the place they had fallen asleep, with no trace of the entity unless physical contact was made.
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">'''Addendum 1''':</span><br><center>'''''Brain Waves'''''</center><br />
Researchers studying brain waves of volunteers and victims using the electroencephalography (EEG) reveal that the EEG initially detects a few bursts of alpha waves before becoming predominantly theta waves. The electromyography (EMG) reveals muscle paralysis with occasional and light muscle twitch activity. These results suggest, like 'traditional' sleep paralysis, Entity 58 appears when one's mind is awake and aware, and one's body is in a state of paralysis. In summary, Entity 58 will approach their paralyzed and vulnerable victim once they enter 'subconscious limbo'.
<br>[[File:Brain waves.jpg|thumb|550x550px|center|<center>This image is of a schematic of typical brain waves detected by the electroencephalogram (EEG).</center>]]<br>
</div>
=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Biology</center></span>'''==
{{Blurimage|file=Wall_spider.png|width=600x600px|align=center|caption=An artistic representation of Manifestation 4 of '''Entity 58''', based on testimonies.}}
It is infeasible to determine whether '''Entity 58''' can invade its victim's mind or is simply invisible to bystanders. During an assault by '''Entity 58''', only the victim themselves can hear, see, and engage with it; other wanderers or entities cannot interact or perceive '''Entity 58'''.

This specific entity takes on many forms; all reported forms are listed below:
==='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>Manifestation 1</center></span>'''===
This manifestation of '''Entity 58''' takes on the appearance of a blurry humanoid; the features of the specific humanoid cannot be determined or described. The subject is described as tall, reaching up to three meters, and has extremely little muscle mass, suggesting malnutrition. Furthermore, this is the most common manifestation reported by the majority of witnesses.
==='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>Manifestation 2</center></span>'''===
Manifestation 2 of '''Entity 58''' is reported as a shadowy and hairless humanoid that stands at 11.5 ft (3.5 m) tall. Similar to Manifestation 1, the subject has little to no muscle mass, suggesting malnutrition. This specific form lacks any form of facial features except for a mouth that extends a third of the way down the creature's chest. However, the mouth of the entity lacks any teeth, tongue, or flesh, instead being described as a void. This form is considered uncommon.
==='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>Manifestation 3</center></span>'''===
This specific manifestation is a massive, dark octopus with its tentacles extending into the fifth dimension and its body violating Euclidean geometry. The surface of the entity is extremely slimy, and many survivors report an odor that is similar to blood originating from the octopus. Manifestation 3 is considered fairly common.
==='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>Manifestation 4</center></span>'''===
Manifestation 4 appears to be a shadowy arachnid, reaching up to a height of 26.5 ft (8 m), with the legs of the creature being exceptionally long and skinny. The entity lacks any form of facial features except for a collection of extremely small, albeit hollow, eyes that will stare directly at the victim. This form is deemed extremely rare.
=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Discovery</center></span>'''==
Before the discovery of '''The Sleep Paralysis Demon''', most wanderers assumed that any mutilated corpse found in the Backrooms was done by a common entity, like [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Entity 6|Dullers]], etc. As previously mentioned, '''Entity 58''' can only be seen by the selected target; due to the property of this entity, many reports regarding a 'sleep demon attacking' were not a concern and hence, were not taken seriously for the following reasons:
* Sleep paralysis is considered a fairly common sleep disturbance among individuals in both [[The Frontrooms]] and [[Backrooms Wiki| The Backrooms]]. It sounded extremely implausible that a sleep disturbance could be a threat to individuals.

* Researchers assumed the rates of sleep paralysis would increase among explorers of [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]] because of the emotional and psychological trauma explorers must endure from isolation and being lost in The Backrooms.

The only indicators of '''Entity 58's''' existence were the following: 
* Many witnesses report seeing other wanderers being attacked, mutilated, and killed by an invisible force while the victim was asleep. 

* Survivors would file reports concerning getting approached, attacked, or taken by this entity in their sleep and returning with corroborating wounds and injuries.

* Investigators and researchers were actively monitoring and examining sleep patterns, behaviors, and experiences reported by explorers in an attempt to find any evidence of this elusive entity.
Eventually, all of the reports and evidence led to the recognition of '''The Sleep Paralysis Demon''' as a legitimate entity.
=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Theories</center></span>'''==
All of these theories are popular among wanderers. 
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">'''Theory I''':</span><br><center>'''''The Lost Wanderer'''''</center><br />
Theory I, also referred to as the Lost Wanderer Theory, suggests that '''Entity 58''' originated from a wanderer who no-clipped into [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]] and began wandering the levels. Eventually, the emotional and psychological trauma led the wanderer to collapse and die from a lack of hydration and malnutrition. Through unknown means, the deceased wanderer gained anomalous abilities, and the enraged spirit of the wanderer decided to start hunting other wanderers sleeping out of frustration.

However, people who disagree with this theory argue that there is a lack of evidence of actual spirits in [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]], and argue that, realistically, they would have more likely succumbed to [[Phenomenon 35]] before they would have died. Nonetheless, this theory is still considered fairly plausible by many wanderers.
</div><br>
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">'''Theory II''':</span><br><center>'''''Failed Experiment'''''</center><br />
Theory II, or the Failed Experiment theory, claims that '''Entity 58''' originated from an experiment conducted by an unidentified organization, likely on a [[Entity 9|faceling]] or a human. The result of this experiment was that the subject was accidentally given anomalous abilities, which resulted in the creation of '''Entity 58''' and the deaths of all researchers conducting the experiment.

However, those who disagree with this theory argue that there is a lack of actual groups who conducts experiments on entities or humans, claiming that if this suspected organization did exist, there would be well-documented experiments on both entities and humans. Nonetheless, Theory II is still considered possible.
</div><br>
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">'''Theory III''':</span><br><center>'''''Entity 58 is just a Dream'''''</center><br />
Theory III argues that '''Entity 58''' itself does not exist, and those who were killed were attacked by another entity. The paralysis that the victims experience is considered to be a nightmare, and the attacks are done by another entity. Furthermore, this theory claims that the reports of wanderers getting attacked and killed in their sleep are a result of optical illusions that were developed as a result of the hostility of [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]].

However, this theory is considered highly inaccurate. While it was significantly more prevalent during the earlier days of '''Entity 58's''' documentation, there has been more recent video documentation of victims getting attacked by an invisible force in their sleep, proving that there is no other entity attacking the victims. 
</div><br>

=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>> Survival Guide</center></span>'''==
Due to '''Entity 58's''' preference for victims who fall asleep on hard surfaces, it is advised that wanderers try to find a soft surface, such as a bed or sleeping bag. While it may be difficult to find such soft surfaces in the hostile environment of [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]], any soft material, such as cotton, will reduce the likelihood of an attack by about 75%. 

If, by any means, an encounter with '''Entity 58''' occurs, one should maintain intense eye contact with the entity and remain still. Although blinking or looking away briefly is unlikely to cause death or disappearance, it is considered extremely risky to break eye contact with '''Entity 58'''. Generally, showing fear will increase the likelihood of a physical attack by '''Entity 58'''; therefore, wanderers who encounter '''Entity 58''' should blankly stare at the demon without any movement. If one follows all of the given instructions, they should wake up in the place where they fell asleep after the encounter is over.
